<br>
 <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=288863>Fitemore Mystique</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwubaogoldenarmz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wubao Goldenarmz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 176<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/1/02 10:37:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4049.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   easiest haste to get in the game ...</span><hr size=1> The easiest to obtain haste items in the game are:<br>
<br>
1) If you're plane capable, the Haste Belts that drop off of mobs in Plane of Air. You spend enough time clearing even just the first island or two, and one's bound to drop. They always seem to drop for the wrong classes when we go up there, though, heh.<br>
<br>
2) If you're not plane capable, then Hollowshade Moor. When the Grimling's have won the war. In the owlbear caves, there'll be a named Grimling Spawn. His RARE drop is a haste belt. Pretty easy to kill him for the belt. The pain is waiting on him to drop it (need patience for that) and getting the Grimlings to be the winners of the war (most people prefer owlbears to have won the war for the pelts ... and for some odd reason, the wolves keep winning the damn war on my server).<br>
<br>
